FBIS4-9923 "drlat064_m_94004" FBIS-LAT-94-064 Daily Report 4 Apr 1994 Brazil Miner Reportedly Shot by Venezuelan Patrol Miner Reportedly Shot by Venezuelan Patrol PY0404125494 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in Portuguese 1000 GMT 4 Apr 94 PY0404125494 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network Portuguese BFN [Text] The Venezuelan National Guard killed a Brazilian miner in the village of Parima, in the country's Amazon region. According to official reports, the Brazilian miner -- who was known as Franco -- shot at a Venezuelan patrol when the patrol found an illegal camp in Parima, which served as a base for gold and diamond mining. Brazilians Antonio Edilmar Ribeiro and Cicero Eduardo Britto were arrested and are being held in Puerto Ayacucho, the capital of the Amazon province.
